<item>
            <title>[NIFI-10449] ScriptedLookupService does not reload the script when disabled then enabled</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NIFI-10449</link>
                <project id="12316020" key="NIFI">Apache NiFi</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently a ScriptedLookupService does not reload the script after it has been disabled. This can cause changes to external values not to be picked up by the controller service when it is re-enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, consider a ScriptedLookupService that loads a lookup table from a parameter. Configure the parameter with some sample mappings and verify it works. Then update the parameter to specify different values. The LookupService keeps returning the original values, but the script should have been re-compiled/evaluated after the controller service was disabled.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
